===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Tehama had a population of 435. The population density was {{convert|547.9|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Tehama was 291 (66.9%) [[White Americans|White]], 6 (1.4%) [[African Americans|African American]], 23 (5.3%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 2 (0.5%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 1 (0.2%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 52 (12.0%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 60 (13.8%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 104 persons (23.9%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Tehama city, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0678106 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 181 households, out of which 59 (32.6%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 76 (42.0%) were married-couple households, 18 (9.9%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 49 (27.1%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 38 (21.0%) had a male householder with no partner present. 53 households (29.3%) were one person, and 29 (16.0%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.4.<ref name=DP1/> There were 111 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (61.3% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Tehama city, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0678106 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 85 people (19.5%) under the age of 18, 36 people (8.3%) aged 18 to 24, 95 people (21.8%) aged 25 to 44, 114 people (26.2%) aged 45 to 64, and 105 people (24.1%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 45.1{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 93.3 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 191 housing units at an average density of {{convert|240.6|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 181 (94.8%) were occupied. Of these, 133 (73.5%) were owner-occupied, and 48 (26.5%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
At the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]] Tehama had a population of 418. The population density was {{convert|526.3|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Tehama was 346 (82.8%) White, 6 (1.4%) African American, 23 (5.5%) Native American, 1 (0.2%) Asian, 0 (0.0%) Pacific Islander, 27 (6.5%) from other races, and 15 (3.6%) from two or more races.  Hispanic or Latino of any race were 57 people (13.6%).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0678106|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715040517/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0678106|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Tehama city|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|accessdate=July 12, 2014}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households, no one lived in non-institutionalized group quarters and no one was institutionalized.

There were 165 households, 48 (29.1%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 92 (55.8%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 15 (9.1%) had a female householder with no husband present, 11 (6.7%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 9 (5.5%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 0 (0%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 38 households (23.0%) were one person and 21 (12.7%) had someone living alone who was 65 or older. The average household size was 2.53.  There were 118 families (71.5% of households); the average family size was 2.98.

The age distribution was 96 people (23.0%) under the age of 18, 24 people (5.7%) aged 18 to 24, 95 people (22.7%) aged 25 to 44, 121 people (28.9%) aged 45 to 64, and 82 people (19.6%) who were 65 or older.  The median age was 44.1 years. For every 100 females, there were 101.0 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 103.8 males.

There were 195 housing units at an average density of 245.5 per square mile, of the occupied units 118 (71.5%) were owner-occupied and 47 (28.5%) were rented. The homeowner vacancy rate was 4.8%; the rental vacancy rate was 11.3%.  281 people (67.2% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 137 people (32.8%) lived in rental housing units.

===2000===
At the [[2000 United States census|2000 census]], the median [[income]] for a household in the city was $27,500, and the median family income  was $35,125. Males had a median income of $25,333 versus $21,667 for females. The per capita income for the city was $13,044.  About 10.6% of families and 16.6% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 33.9% of those under age 18 and 4.5% of those age 65 or over.<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=January 31, 2008|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref>

